inference:
We are asked to compute $\arcsin \left( -\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \right).$  We want to find an angle $\theta$ such that $\sin(\theta) = -\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$ and $-\frac{\pi}{2} \le \theta \le \frac{\pi}{2}.$

Since $\sin \left( -\frac{\pi}{3} \right) = -\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2},$ we have $\arcsin \left( -\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \right) = -\frac{\pi}{3}.$

Final Answer: $\boxed{-\frac{\pi}{3}}$
